  "prompt": "What do we call video with words on it?",
  "response": "Video with words on it is commonly referred to as \"text overlays\" or \"captioned video.\" If the words are part of the video's content or used to convey a message, it may also be called \"subtitles\" or \"titles.\" In a broader sense, if the video is designed to convey information with visuals and text together, it can be considered \"text-based video\" or \"typography video.\"",
